OL,7,F"When with any government authority
OL,8,Fthere's any idea of negligence, gross
OL,9,Fnegligence, or a death has happened,
OL,10,Fthat independent regulatory body gets
OL,11,Fto oversee the various different
OL,12,Finvestigations and the evidence. "
OL,14,F"It would have the power to
OL,15,Finvestigate itself, and have the power
OL,16,Fto bring forward prosecutions."
OL,18,FHe has also passed a body of evidence
OL,19,Fto police in Wales, and says the Crown
OL,20,FProsecution Service, or CPS, are
OL,21,Fexamining it.
